Sentencas: Cathodes demonstrating elevated electrochemical catalysis and CO2 endurance are fundamental for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Enhanced oxygen reduction kinetics of SrCoO3-δ by Ta/Cu or Nb/Cu co-doping as high-performance cathodes for SOFC

Sentencas: Herein, Ta/Cu co-doped SrCo0.8Ta0.1Cu0.1O3-delta (SCTC) and Nb/Cu co-doped SrCo0.8Nb0.1-Cu0.1O3-delta (SCNC) perovskite oxides were prepared and comparative studied as high-performance SOFC cathodes.
Titulo: Enhanced oxygen reduction kinetics of SrCoO3-δ by Ta/Cu or Nb/Cu co-doping as high-performance cathodes for SOFC

Sentencas: Due to the synergistic effects of Ta/Cu and Nb/Cu, the oxygen vacancy content, the ratio of Co3+/Co4+, the average bonding energy and the critical radius in the material are well regulated, resulting in the reduction of TEC and enhanced electrochemical catalytic activity in SCTC and SCNC.
Titulo: Enhanced oxygen reduction kinetics of SrCoO3-δ by Ta/Cu or Nb/Cu co-doping as high-performance cathodes for SOFC

Sentencas: At 800 degrees C, SCTC exhibits an ASR of 0.033 omega cm2, while it is 0.038 omega cm2 for SCNC.
Titulo: Enhanced oxygen reduction kinetics of SrCoO3-δ by Ta/Cu or Nb/Cu co-doping as high-performance cathodes for SOFC

Sentencas: Additionally, SCTC demonstrates a considerable output per-formance of 0.89 W cm-2, representing a 15.65% improvement over SCNC.
Titulo: Enhanced oxygen reduction kinetics of SrCoO3-δ by Ta/Cu or Nb/Cu co-doping as high-performance cathodes for SOFC

Sentencas: This work offers a highly effective approach to developing materials for next-generation energy transformation devices.
Titulo: Enhanced oxygen reduction kinetics of SrCoO3-δ by Ta/Cu or Nb/Cu co-doping as high-performance cathodes for SOFC
